cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.CR, cs.NE 

This paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it proposes a new approach for training and inference of deep neural networks. It also involves experiments on various datasets to evaluate the performance of the proposed method. 

It is also likely to belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision) as the experiments are conducted on image datasets and the proposed method involves sampling mixup images using the latent manifold underlying the data. 

Additionally, it could belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as it involves improving the robustness of deep neural networks to adversarial attacks. 

It could also belong to cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) as it involves defending against adversarial attacks on deep neural networks. 

Finally, it could belong to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as it involves training deep neural networks using a novel approach.
